Please follow these configuration steps after installation. You can also refer this page in your Salesforce tab to setup new buttons.
After creating custom list button; for lightning experience, click 'Search Layouts for Salesforce Classic' in the same object setup. For Classic Experience, click 'Search Layouts'.
Click dropdown next to the 'List View' and click 'Edit' for Lightning Experience. For Salesforce Classic, edit 'Account List View' option.
Add the list button created in previous step to 'Selected Buttons' from the 'Available Buttons' section.
Enable List Button for List View
For Lightning Experience, go to Setup > Object Manager > Select custom/standard object. For Classic, go to Setup > Search for object in search bar.
Example:- If the object is Contact then the complete URL should be: /apex/Export2Excel?ObjectType={!$ObjectType.Contact}
Click 'Buttons Links and Actions' > Click 'New Button or Link'.
Name Label and API Name as 'Export'.
Select 'Display Type' as 'List Button'and 'Behavior as 'Display in existing window with sidebar'.
After ObjectType=, insert object API name of the object for which you are setting the list button.
Example:- If the object API name is 'Custom_Object__c' then the complete URL should be: /apex/Export2Excel?ObjectType=Custom_Object__c
